data.name: text
data.value: The word logorrhoea is often used pejoratively  to describe prose that is highly abstract and  contains little concrete language. Since abstract  writing is hard to visualize, it often seems as though  it makes no sense and all the words are excessive.  Writers in academic fields that concern themselves mostly  with the abstract, such as philosophy and especially  postmodernism, often fail to include extensive concrete  examples of their ideas, and so a superficial examination  of their work might lead one to believe that it is all nonsense.

description:
This API can be used to compute a set of readability metrics for a given text. We currently support the following metrics: Automated Readability Index, Coleman-Liau Index, FleschKincaid Grade Level, Flesch Reading Ease, Gunning-Fog Index, SMOG score, and SMOG Index.

The service is deployed at Google App Engine and available at https://ipeirotis-hrd.appspot.com/

The code and documentation are available on Github at https://github.com/ipeirotis/ReadabilityMetrics
